2026-06-16 | Process String With Special Characters

	Question
Return the resulting string after applying all operations.
	Key Insight
This is a direct simulation problem.
We maintain the current string result and process each character according to its meaning.
	Approach
1.	Initialize:
			result = ""
2.	Traverse every character c in s.
3.	If c is a lowercase letter:
			append c
4.	If c is '*':
			remove last character if present
5.	If c is '#':
			result = result + result
6.	If c is '%':
			reverse(result)
7.	Return result.
	Time Complexity
	O(n + total length of generated string)
	Space Complexity
	O(length of final string)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    string processString(string s) {
        string result;
        for(char ch : s) {
            if(ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') {
                result.push_back(ch);
            }
            else if(ch == '*') {
                if(!result.empty())
                    result.pop_back();
            }
            else if(ch == '#') {
                result += result;
            }
            else if(ch == '%') {
                reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
};
	Key Insight
The operations affect only the current state of the string, so a straightforward simulation from left to right correctly produces the final result.
